# Cedar Lawn Company — build-time environment
# Copy to `.env` for local dev, and set the same value in your host's build env (Netlify/Cloudflare/etc).

# WHERE LEADS GO. Without this, "Text to book" and the out-of-area form only log to the
# browser console and are LOST. Point it at a keyless public form sink — a public URL,
# not a secret, so the no-API-key rule still holds. Good options (free tiers):
#   Formspree:  https://formspree.io           ->  https://formspree.io/f/XXXXXXXX
#   Basin:      https://usebasin.com           ->  https://usebasin.com/f/XXXXXXXX
#   Netlify Forms / a tiny serverless function also work.
# It receives a JSON POST: { type, address, county, areaSqft, tier, price, cadence, contact, business, at }
VITE_LEAD_ENDPOINT=
